OL,3,CIslamophopia 'has increased' after
OL,4,CSouthport riots, survey finds
OL,6,FA majority of muslims feel that
OL,7,FIslamophobia has increased following
OL,8,Fthe attack in Southport and the
OL,9,Fdisturbances which followed.
OL,11,FThe charity Tell Mama analysed, as
OL,12,Fpart of the annual No2H8 campaign, the
OL,13,Fopinions of 750 Muslims across the UK
OL,14,Feight weeks after disorder broke out
OL,15,Ffollowing the fatal stabbings of three
OL,16,Fyoung girls in Southport.
OL,18,FIt was found that just under three-
OL,19,Fquarters, 71%, felt anti-Muslim hatred
OL,20,Fand Islamophobia had become more
OL,21,Fwidespread since the unrest.
